results.snippet: Thirty-five new employees of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration will report to work tomorrow morning at the Johnson Space Center at Houston. After formal words of welcome and the usual filling out of personnel forms, they will plunge...
results.lead_paragraph: Thirty-five new employees of the National Aeronautics and Space Administration will report to work tomorrow morning at the Johnson Space Center at Houston. After formal words of welcome and the usual filling out of personnel forms, they will plunge into a two-year program of study and training in space flight, for they are the newest class of astronaut candidates, the first selected in 11 years.
